  - STATE_UPDATE: {'commit_analysis_result': "The HAFix analysis is complete. Let me summarize the findings.\n\n---\n\n## HAFix Analysis Complete\n\n### Summary\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Suspect SHA** | `1d5755d81c5fb00218f04925b5dbc2f312749547` |\n| **Attribution** | **DOWNSTREAM** |\n| **Target Fix Path** | `/home/senchen/temp/fix_build_agent/oss-fuzz/projects/cert-manager/` |\n\n### Root Cause Chain\n\n1. **OSS-Fuzz commit `9ca5b1054`** bumped Go from 1.23.4 → 1.25.0 in the base-builder image's `install_go.sh`\n2. **cert-manager commit `1d5755d81`** bumped Go from 1.25.0 → 1.25.7 in `go.mod`\n3. The `go-118-fuzz-build` v2 tool (used by `compile_native_go_fuzzer_v2`) creates an **overlay JSON file** that replaces `testing/fuzz.go` in the Go standard library\n4. In Go 1.25+, the Go toolchain is stored under **GOMODCACHE** (`/root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64/`)\n5. Go 1.25+ **prohibits** overlay replacements beneath GOMODCACHE, causing the build to panic\n\n### Why DOWNSTREAM?\n\nThe error is not caused by a bug in the cert-manager source code. It's an **infrastructure incompatibility** between:\n- The `go-118-fuzz-build` tool (which creates overlays under GOMODCACHE)\n- Go 1.25+ (which prohibits overlays under GOMODCACHE)\n\nThe fix should be applied to the **OSS-Fuzz project configuration** (`build.sh` or `Dockerfile`) to work around this toolchain issue, e.g., by patching the overlay generation or using a different approach to build the native Go fuzzers."}
