  - STATE_UPDATE: {'solution_plan': "The solution.txt looks correct. Let me now provide the final summary.\n\n[AUTONOMOUS]: No specific rule from Expert Knowledge Patterns directly addresses the Go 1.25+ GOMODCACHE overlay restriction; the fix was derived from independent analysis of the `go-118-fuzz-build_v2` source code and Go toolchain behavior.\n\n## Fix Summary\n\n**Root Cause**: The `go-118-fuzz-build_v2` tool creates a Go build overlay JSON that replaces `$GOROOT/src/testing/fuzz.go`. In Go 1.25+, when a project's `go.mod` requires a newer Go version (1.25.7), `go env GOROOT` returns a path under GOMODCACHE (`/root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64`). Go 1.25+ strictly prohibits overlay replacements beneath GOMODCACHE, causing the build to fail with a panic.\n\n**Fix**: Modified `build.sh` to:\n1. Download Go 1.25.7 to a non-GOMODCACHE location (`/root/.go.1.25.7`)\n2. Set `GOROOT=/root/.go.1.25.7` and `GOTOOLCHAIN=local` so `go-118-fuzz-build_v2` creates overlay entries targeting a path outside GOMODCACHE\n3. Update `PATH` to use the new Go binary\n\n**File modified**: `/home/senchen/temp/fix_build_agent/oss-fuzz/projects/cert-manager/build.sh`"}
